---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Me" description="About Sofia — Sofiverse, Product and Graphic Designer">

  <section class="about">
    <div class="container">

      <a href="/" class="back-link">← go back to home</a>

      <h1 class="about__title">About Me</h1>

      <div class="about__grid">

        <div class="about__image">
          <img src="/img-sofiverse.jpg" alt="Sofia — Sofiverse" />
        </div>

        <div class="about__text">
          <p>My name is Sofia (a.k.a. Sofiverse) and I'm a Product and Graphic Designer with a background in Architecture.</p>

          <p>After leading multidisciplinary teams in housing projects and collaborating with international organizations like the UN and GIZ, I discovered web3 in 2022 (and fell in love). I transitioned into tech, where I combine my passion for design and systems thinking to create intuitive digital experiences.</p>

          <p>Over the past four years, I've designed coordination platforms and dApps for open-source, funding, and regenerative projects that strengthen the onchain economy, impact, and reputation systems. I thrive in collaborative environments and am driven by the opportunity to build meaningful tools that improve how Web3 communities operate.</p>

          <p>I work with technical teams who built something good but can't get the rest of the world to see why.</p>

          <p>That gap, between what an engineering team knows and what an outsider sees, is what I close. Sometimes the answer is a product surface that finally clicks. Sometimes it's a landing page that says what it means. Sometimes it's a content system that helps a team explain itself without burning out. The problem is one; the solutions look different depending on where the breakage is.</p>

          <p>If you're building something technical and you can feel that gap, you know where to find me.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-24);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-inline: var(--space-8);
  }

  /* ── Back link ── */
  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-link);
    color: var(--color-text-ghost);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  /* ── Page title ── */
  .about__title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-h3);
    font-weight: 400;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* ── Two-column grid ── */
  .about__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 43fr 57fr;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ── Image ── */
  .about__image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── Text ── */
  .about__text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about__text p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-8);
    }

    .about__title {
      font-size: var(--text-h4);
    }
  }
</style>
